kavli institute for particle physics and cosmology school of humanities and sciences skip to content skip to main navigation stanford university graduate & undergraduate studies h&s intranet faculty affairs stanford alumni search stanford university school of humanities & sciences about h&s leadership departments & programs news & events faculty faces of h&s giving departments listing departments & programs kavli institute for particle physics and cosmology stanford physicists aim to unlock the deepest secrets of our universe at the kavli institute for particle astrophysics and cosmology the institute is based on campus and at the slac national accelerator laboratory kavli researchers played a leading role for example in developing the fermi gamma ray space telescope which science magazine recognized as a top 10 breakthrough in 2009 some institute scientists are now designing the world's largest digital camera to capture images from a giant telescope and create a 3 d map of the universe other projects at kipac include the observation of the active sun at the solar dynamics observatory as well as the search for individual particles of dark matter by the cryogenic dark matter search related links kipac researchers track binary black holes study reveals milky way among oddball four percent visit the stanford kipac website kavli foundation website contact us follow us on twitter make a gift to h&s copyright 1997 2012 stanford university all rights reserved
